Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Sentencing proceeded. Statements made by State, defense and defendant.  Additional statement by LaMitria S.
 
As to Count 1 as amended: 
The Court sentenced the defendant to a MAXIMUM TERM OF IMPRISONMENT of 51 MONTHS, CONSECUTIVE to any other time being served with credit for 133 days served. The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prison System is 15 MONTHS.  The MAXIMUM TERM OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION IS 36 MONTHS.

The defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:
*No new law violations rising to the level of probable cause;
*Cooperate with any and all rules set forth by the probation agent;
*Obtain AODA assessment and successfully complete follow-up treatment;
*Random urine screens;
*No drug dealing or association with drug community (drug users/dealers or drug houses);
*Obtain/maintain full time employment or full time school and part time employment;
*Participate in a cognitive thinking program;
*Department is to assess for vocational needs and relevant programming, defendant to follow through with any recommendations;
*Provide DNA sample (if not already provided)- pay surcharge;
*Pay all applicable mandatory surcharges, fees, assessments, and costs; 
The Court ordered restitution $0.00.  The Court ordered that all financial obligations and/or restitution be paid through collection of sums by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b) and as a condition of extended supervision.  Any amount remaining due and owing is subject to civil judgment.

Appeal rights given. Rights as they pertain to votiing and firearms given as well. 

